text: Dennis "Boog" Highberger (born September 26, 1959) is an American politician. He was a City Council member in Lawrence, Kansas from 2003 to 2009. He was also Lawrence's mayor from 2005 to 2006. He graduated from the University of Kansas School of Law in 1992. He was an attorney with the Kansas Department of Health and Environment from 1992 to 2011. He has been a Democratic member for the 46th district in the Kansas House of Representatives since 2015."Boog" Highberger, Project Vote Smart.
